Package pathfinder.informed

Class MazeProblem

  • java.lang.Object
    • pathfinder.informed.MazeProblem

  • public class MazeProblem
extends java.lang.Object
    Specifies the Maze Grid pathfinding problem including the actions, transitions, goal test, and solution test. Can be fed as an input to a Search algorithm to find and then test a solution.

      • getCost

        public int getCost​(pathfinder.informed.MazeState state)
        Returns cost of an action depending on the type of tile is for the current position The cost to move to a Goal state is 1 unit, the cost to move to an Initial state is 1 unit, the cost to move to a Mud tile is 3 units, the cost to move to a wall is not applicable, since it is not possible to move to a wall, and the cost to move to a Key state is 1 unit
        Parameters:
        state - A MazeState(col, row) to test
        Returns:
        Integer equating to the total cost to move to the given tile

      • getTransitions

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,pathfinder.informed.MazeState> getTransitions​(pathfinder.informed.MazeState state)
        Returns a map of the states that can be reached from the given input state using any of the available actions.
        Parameters:
        state - A MazeState (col, row) representing the current state from which actions can be taken
        Returns:
        Map A map of actions to the states that they lead to, of the format, for current MazeState (c, r):
        { "U": (c, r-1), "D": (c, r+1), "L": (c-1, r), "R": (c+1, r) }

      • testSolution

        public int[] testSolution​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> possibleSoln)
        Given a possibleSoln, tests to ensure that it is indeed a solution to this MazeProblem, as well as returning the cost.
        Parameters:
        possibleSoln - A possible solution to test, which is a list of actions of the format: ["U", "D", "D", "L", ...]
        Returns:
        A 2-element array of ints of the format [isSoln, cost] where: isSoln will be 0 if it is not a solution, and 1 if it is cost will be an integer denoting the cost of the given solution to test optimality
